This is Veles Core universal amd64 Linux release. 


## Installation
To install, enter directory containing this README file and simply 
run following command:

make install

This will perform standard installation including Veles Core
command-line and graphical interfaces, manual pages 
and desktop icon.

Alternative modes of installation:
make install-cli	Installs daemon and command-line client only
make install-gui	Installs only graphical interface, no daemon


## Ubuntu and Debian notes
On Ubuntu and Debian-based systems the preferred way of installing 
Veles Core is from our APT repository, or manually from .deb files.

To install or update from official Veles Core repository, switch
to root account and run following commands:

apt-key adv --fetch-keys http://apt.veles.network/apt.veles.network.gpg.key
add-apt-repository http://apt.veles.network/ubuntu
apt-get update
apt-get install veles 

Available packages:
veles		Virtual package, installs velesd and veles-cli
velesd		Daemon and command-line client
veles-qt	Official graphical user interface
veles-tx	Transaction manipulation utility

Experimental packages:
veles-build-env	Prepares build environment to compile Veles Coure 
		from sources.

